int-org-section.p:
The Administrator is supported by one Associate Administrator and nine Assistant Secretaries-General. Offices and divisions at the secretariat include Offices of the Human Development Report, Audit and Investigations, Ethics, and Independent Evaluation; Global Services Solution and Global Policy Centres; a Crisis Bureau; and also Bureaux for Policy and Programme Support, External Relations and Advocacy, and Management Services. Five Regional Bureaux cover Africa; Asia and the Pacific; the Arab states; Europe and the Commonwealth of Independent States; and Latin America and the Caribbean. The UNDP Administrator acts as the Vice-Chair of the UN Sustainable Development Group (UNSDG, in which UNDP participates), and chairs the UNSDG’s Core Group (see 
UN Development Coordination Office
).
